A banking application passes all planned tests, but business stakeholders still decide to delay release because they lack confidence in the system.
Questions:

What testing objective relates directly to stakeholder confidence?
Why might passing tests not be sufficient to build trust?
What additional testing-related actions could help improve confidence?

Answers:
1. A relevant testing objective would help with stakeholder confidence
2. Continuous testing may not cover business risks or real-world use
3. Test reporting and stakeholder involvement may help.
